details.Implemented size: 4096 bytes = (2 banks) x (8 words per bank) x (256 bytes per word)

Additional information.text: Shallow memory implemented in RAMs instead of MLABs because MLABs cannot be configured in true dual-port mode.
RAM usage is increased from 128 RAMs to 256 RAMs because the width of individual RAM blocks in true dual-port mode is limited to 20 bits.
In each private copy:</br>  Variable 'hash_map' occupies memory words [0-12] and has 1 array element split across 13 memory words.</br>  Memory words [13-15] are unused padding.
